The bar chart illustrates the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on the beauty habits of Romanian women in 2020. It shows three categories: "I took more care of myself" with a value of 63, "I tried new products/I did things I was not able to do until now" with a value of 43, and "I had less time for my personal care and make-up" with a value of 27.

The bar chart illustrates the circulation volume of euro banknotes in the euro area from January 2002 to January 2020, measured in billions. The data shows an overall increase over the years, starting at 7.8 billion in 2002 and reaching 25.1 billion by 2020. Each year marks a consistent rise in the total volume of euro banknotes in circulation within the euro area.

The bar chart illustrates changes in consumer behavior during the COVID-19 pandemic in Romania in 2020. It shows that 90% of consumers washed fresh products more carefully than before, 75% preferred local products over imported ones, 50% bought more fresh fruits, 45% purchased more health-related products, and 43% increased their purchase of fresh vegetables.

The histogram illustrates public opinion on the effectiveness of athletes refusing to compete in scheduled league games to bring attention to police brutality and racial inequality in the United States as of August 2020. The bar chart illustrates model preferences of prospective buyers in the business aviation industry worldwide from Q3 2019 to Q2 2020, by aircraft model. Other models like Embraer Praetor 600, Caravan 208B, Embraer Phenom 300, Gulfstream G-600, Global 7500, Falcon 6X, and Gulfstream G-500 have lower preference scores ranging from 4.2 to 5.0.

The histogram illustrates the number of national parliament members (deputies) per 100,000 inhabitants in various European Union and UK countries as of 2020. Malta leads with 14.3 deputies, followed by Luxembourg at 10.0, and Cyprus with 9.3. Estonia has 7.8 deputies, while Latvia and Lithuania have 5.0 and 5.1 respectively. The data also includes figures for other countries like Sweden, Greece, and Spain, which have lower numbers of deputies ranging from 1.0 to 3.6 per 100,000 inhabitants.

The bar chart illustrates the total population of the Île-de-France region in 2018, broken down by area. Paris has a population of 2 million, while the inner suburbs account for 4.2 million individuals. The greater suburbs have a population of 4.9 million. When summed up, the total population of the Île-de-France region is 11.1 million.

The bar chart illustrates public opinion on the spread of COVID-19 in Australia for 2020, broken down by time frame and outcome. It shows three categories: "Will get better" with percentages of 5% in one month, 20% in three months, and 58% in one year; "Will get worse" with percentages of 83% in one month, 63% in three months, and 24% in one year; and "Don't know" with percentages of 2% in one month, 7% in three months, and 15% in one year.

The line chart illustrates the monthly average prices for normal wheat in Egypt from January 2019 to July 2020, measured in Egyptian pounds per kilogram. The data points show fluctuations over the period, with prices starting at 8.5 in January 2019 and generally decreasing over time. By July 2020, the price had dropped to 7.2. The line chart illustrates the decrease in tourism spending in Los Angeles due to the COVID-19 pandemic in 2020. It shows two data points: pre-coronavirus spending of $25 billion and post-coronavirus spending of $12 billion, indicating a significant loss of $13 billion in tourism revenue as a result of the pandemic.

The line chart illustrates the number of enterprises in the postal service market within the U.S. from 2018 to 2021. In 2018, there were 50 enterprises, which increased to 55 by 2019 and then slightly decreased to 54 in 2020. The following year saw a slight rise to 56 enterprises.

The bar chart illustrates the rates of substance use and suicide ideation among different education levels in the U.S. during COVID-19 in 2020. Individuals with less than a high school diploma report a 22% increase in substance use to cope with pandemic-related stressors and a 30% rate of seriously considering suicide within the past 30 days. Those with a high school diploma show a 15% increase in substance use and a 13% suicide ideation rate. Those with some college education have an 11% increase in substance use and an 8% suicide ideation rate, while those with a bachelor's degree report a 14% increase in substance use and an 11% suicide ideation rate. Professional degree holders indicate a 12% increase in substance use and a 10% suicide ideation rate. The 'Unknown' category shows a 10% increase in substance use and a 6% suicide ideation rate.

The bar chart illustrates the impact of COVID-19 on job posts online in Spain, comparing 2020 to 2019 across various expertise categories. Health-related jobs saw a decrease from 14,000 to 9,500, while computing and IT roles increased from 6,000 to 7,500. Engineering positions dropped from 16,000 to 8,000, whereas marketing and sales jobs rose from 8,000 to 9,000. The bar chart illustrates the share of professional investors who increased their ESG (Environmental, Social, and Governance) investments worldwide in 2020 and 2021. In 2020, 74% of investors increased their ESG investments, 14% did not, and 12% were unsure. By 2021, the percentage of investors who increased their ESG investments rose to 82%, while those who did not decreased to 9%, and the unsure category remained at 10%.

The bar chart illustrates the popularity of various music genres in Russia for different age groups in 2020. Pop songs lead with 18 votes from the 18-24 years group, while folk songs have the highest number of votes among older age groups, peaking at 45 votes for those aged 60 and older. Rock is preferred by younger generations, with 42 votes from the 18-24 years group, whereas war songs are most popular among the 45-59 years group with 34 votes. The data includes a range of genres such as bard songs, old romances, jazz, symphonic, tourist, hiking, opera, operetta, marches, "thug" songs, revolutionary songs, and others, each with varying levels of popularity across the five age groups.

The bar chart illustrates the share of adults in Russia who play various musical instruments, categorized by gender in 2020. It shows that males play plucked strings (23%), wind instruments (8%), and percussion (5%) more frequently than females. In contrast, females have a higher participation rate in playing wind instruments (14%), plucked strings (8%), and other instruments (76%). Percussion is equally played by both genders at 5%, while females lead in playing bowed strings (1%) and other instruments (76%). The data also indicates that 2% of males cannot play any musical instrument compared to 1% of females.

The pie chart illustrates the share of consumers purchasing sustainable gifts for Christmas in the UK in 2020, categorized by age groups. The 18-24 age group accounts for 25% of such purchases, while those aged 25-34 make up 20%. The 35-44 age bracket represents 17%, and the 45-54 group contributes 12%. Those aged 55-64 purchase 10%, and the 65+ age group makes up 9% of the sustainable gift buyers. Additionally, all adults combined represent 15% of the purchases.
